Phocaeorum. The Phocaeans, to escape the Persian yoke, migrated B.c. 534 from Asia Minor to Corsica and Marseilles. Cf. Herod. 1. 165. It is said that Sertorius, the famous leader of the anti-Sullan party in Spain, also contemplated sailing away into the Atlantic.
